Branching  

# git branch 
//Lists all local branches 

# git checkout -b <new-branch-name>
// To create branch

# git checkout <new-branch-name> 
// Switches  different branch.

# git merge <branch_name2>
// merge and changes of the branch2 into your current active branch1.

# git checkout main      // But final push will be from main branch.


Merge conflict
Step 1: 
# git checkout main
# vim app.py
# git add app.py
# git commit -m "Initial commit"

Step 2: Create "Branch-A" 
#git checkout -b branch-a
# vim app.py
# git add app.py
# git commit -m "Modified by A"

Step 3: Create "Branch-B" and 
# git checkout main
# git checkout -b branch-b
# vim app.py
# git add app.py
# git commit -m "Modified by B"

Step 4: The Conflict (Merging)
# git merge branch-a
Output: CONFLICT (content): Merge conflict in app.py 










Step 5: Resolve the Conflict
# vim app.py		///To fix it and make it final version
# git add app.py
# git commit -m "Resolved "


Step 6: Finalize the Merge and Push
# git checkout main
# git merge branch-b
# git push origin main


